<details class="gov-details halo-panel">
    <summary class="gov-details__summary">SteamCMD: install and download</summary>
    <div class="gov-details__text">
        <p class="gov-body">
            SteamCMD is Valve’s official command-line Steam client. Official documentation:
            <a target="_blank" href="https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/SteamCMD">https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/SteamCMD</a>
        </p>

        <h4 class="gov-heading-m">Install</h4>
        <ol class="gov-steps">
            <li class="gov-body">
                Download SteamCMD for your platform from Valve’s wiki and extract it:
                <a target="_blank" href="https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/SteamCMD">https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/SteamCMD</a>
            </li>
            <li class="gov-body">Run SteamCMD once so it self-updates.</li>
        </ol>

        <h4 class="gov-heading-m">Run the generated command</h4>
        <ol class="gov-steps">
            <li class="gov-body">
                Paste the generated SteamCMD command and replace:
                <ul class="gov-list">
                    <li class="gov-body"><code>&lt;install-dir&gt;</code> with the desired install folder</li>
                    <li class="gov-body"><code>&lt;user&gt;</code> and <code>&lt;pass&gt;</code> with your Steam credentials</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li class="gov-body">Keep the terminal open while the download completes.</li>
        </ol>

        <details class="gov-details">
            <summary class="gov-details__summary">Login without embedding credentials</summary>
            <div class="gov-details__text">
                <p class="gov-body">
                    To avoid credentials in logs/history, login interactively:
                </p>
                <pre class="gov-pre"><code>steamcmd
login &lt;user&gt;
force_install_dir &lt;install-dir&gt;
download_depot &lt;appid&gt; &lt;depotid&gt; &lt;manifestid&gt;
quit</code></pre>
            </div>
        </details>

        <details class="gov-details">
            <summary class="gov-details__summary">Useful links</summary>
            <div class="gov-details__text">
                <ul class="gov-list">
                    <li class="gov-body"><a target="_blank" href="https://developer.valvesoftware.com/wiki/SteamCMD">SteamCMD official documentation</a></li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </details>
    </div>
</details>
